main event: An unidentified object was sighted in Kiel, Wisconsin on July 6, 1965, resembling a shooting star with a flashing light.
interesting points: The object moved in a complete orbit across the sky in less than one minute.,It had a flashing light that blinked on and off as it crossed the zenith.,The size of the object was comparable to a star.,There was a clear sky with no sound emitted from the object.,The sighting was definitively ruled out as a meteor or balloon, and other logical explanations were considered insufficient.
sighted object: an unidentified object resembling a shooting star with a flashing light
witness description: A civilian observer with knowledge of sky observations, familiar with satellites and aircraft.
